# Power calculator

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
The Power Calculator is a simple online tool used to calculate the statistical power of experimental designs.

## Purpose
This tool helps researchers and practitioners understand the power of their experimental design to detect treatment effects, ensuring that their experiments are adequately powered to produce reliable results.

## How it works
Users can choose between standard and clustered designs, inputting relevant parameters such as sample size, effect size, and significance level. The calculator then provides an estimate of the statistical power for the specified design.

## Requirements
Understanding of Statistical Analysis and Power Statistics is necessary to effectively use this tool.

## Reflections
The most challenging aspect of using the Power Calculator is obtaining accurate estimates of real-world variation in the population of interest.

## Related methods (if any)
This tool is commonly used in conjunction with data analysis and experimentation methods.
